xhtml:div.xhtml:p:
- Package management: using conda in our workflow.
- Build system:
- xeus stack: CI-based build system for conda in QuantForge. (Similar to conda-forge).
- xtensor stack: both available on conda-forge and QuantForge
- Continuous integration:
- OS X and Linux Build with Travis CI. (Mostly gtest and py.test)
- Architecture-dependent CI run on travis with qemu.
- Other tests run periodically on local hardware.
- Continuous benchmarking! For xtensor only, on local hardware.
- Further continuous integration tests downstream, with the CRAN and Debian CI.

xhtml:p.xhtml:font:
xwidgets and other widgets libraries built upon it don't depend on the C++ interpreter. They just happen to be usable in that context.
They can be used with any kernel based on xeus.

xhtml:p.xhtml:font:
xtensor foundational package for cross-language data structures for data sciences.
- expression system: separate data format from how one operates on data: enables adaptors

- C++ performances: continuously benchmarked agains Eigen.
- used to create extension modules and numerical packages for multiple target languages (native C++, R, Python, Julia). Be as simple to use as numpy
- also at the foundation of C++ widgets packages like xthreejs, xvolume, soon xplot.

xhtml:p.xhtml:span: Xeus' concurrency model allows for control messages to be processed while client code is running, while it is not the case for ipykernel.
The problem of handling debugging messages can be solved once with xeus, and leveraged in all target languages.
